         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Cambewarra, Shoalhaven, New South Wales, ¶ April 13th 1890. ¶ Honored Sir, ¶  ¶ We have been successful in obtaining flowers of the tree, whose fruit, leaves, and bark, I sent you some time ago, ¶  an...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.04.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Weir</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M45, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Endiandra sieberi</seg> (MEL 582703).</p>
               </note>Cambewarra, Shoalhaven, New South Wales,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">April 13th 1890.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Honored Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have been successful in obtaining flowers of the tree, whose fruit, leaves, and bark, I sent you some time ago,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">T. Weir to M, 22 February 1890.</p>
               </note> and which you declared to be new to you. I am surprised at finding the flowers at this time of the year; the tree is damaged by fire at the root which probably accounts for its flowring at this time. We discovered the flowers with the aid of a small telescope; we did not fall the tree, so we can get more flowers if the enclosed sprays get damaged in transit.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, yours respectfully.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thomas Weir.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
